The paper deals with communication complexity and lower bounds for sampling and duplicate finding in streams, which are topics typically studied in theoretical computer science. Specifically, the paper provides optimal lower bounds for the universal relation problem, which is a classic problem in communication complexity (cs.CC). The paper also applies these lower bounds to obtain optimal lower bounds for sampling and duplicate finding in streams, which are problems related to data structures and information theory (cs.DS, cs.IT). Additionally, the paper uses techniques from differential privacy and randomized reductions, which are topics studied in cryptography and algorithms (cs.CR, cs.DM).
